Ahile thachaina but it was all the rage in early 2000s, we didn't play but exchanged pokemon cards that we got with uncle chips and Cheetos.

Not really. I think I stopped at just over 100 different dinosaurs. I used to watch a cartoon show called Dino King and started tabulating them from there. I noted info in the same order that the cards had in the show; Name with Picture of habitat, and after I tabulated all of the dinosaurs shown there, I just...stopped.

Probably some of those are fictional, but I definitely remember most as being actually real since I later started using google to confirm my drawings (It got "lost" 2 years ago) and I distinctly remember some dinosaurs that I could not believe were actually real. For eg. Pachycephalosaurus; I still can't believe this thing is real cuz of my memories of it shooting laser beams in the cartoon.

Tldr; No, I kinda stopped at \~100 and then it got lost 2 years ago. It had names, coloring and habitat description.
